[src:simplex-algorithm/duality-optimization] According to George Dantzig, the duality theorem for linear optimization was conjectured by John von Neumann immediately after Dantzig presented the linear programming problem.
[src:simplex-algorithm/duality-optimization] Von Neumann noted that he was using information from his game theory, and conjectured that two person zero sum matrix game was equivalent to linear programming.
[src:simplex-algorithm/duality-optimization] Rigorous proofs were first published in 1948 by Albert W.
