[src:simplex-algorithm/ellipsoid-method] *x* is in *G***, where *f* is a convex function and *G* is a convex set (a subset of an Euclidean space *Rn*).
[src:simplex-algorithm/ellipsoid-method] Each problem *p* in the family is represented by a data-vector Data(*p*), e.g., the real-valued coefficients in matrices and vectors representing the function *f* and the feasible region *G*.
