[src:simplex-algorithm/interior-point-method] We assume that we can compute efficiently the value of *b*, its gradient, and its Hessian, for every point x in the interior of *G*.
[src:simplex-algorithm/interior-point-method] We define the path of minimizers by: **x*(t) := arg min ft(x)**.
[src:simplex-algorithm/interior-point-method] We approximate this path along an increasing sequence *ti*.
